  "bodyText": "MiniMax 2.7 & Kimi K2.5 are free on Zo Zo · Pricing About Newsletter Blog Resources Download Get started Back to Skills Run in Zo video-frames Extract frames or short clips from videos using ffmpeg. Clawdbot Video Frames (ffmpeg) Extract a single frame from a video, or create quick thumbnails for inspection. Quick start First frame: {baseDir}/scripts/frame.sh /path/to/video.mp4 --out /tmp/frame.jpg Copy At a timestamp: {baseDir}/scripts/frame.sh /path/to/video.mp4 --time 00:00:10 --out /tmp/frame-10s.jpg Copy Notes Prefer --time for “what is happening around here?”. Use a .jpg for quick share; use .png for crisp UI frames. Preview - Open in Zo to view the full skill. PRODUCT Documentation Blog Newsletter Comparisons Pricing Skills Integrations Channels Models Product Updates INFORMATION FAQ Careers Brand Terms Privacy Help Center Contact Security COMMUNITY Discord LinkedIn X @zocomputer YouTube Testimonials Ambassadors Merch Zo Computer Company"
